request.description:
Stream real-time execution events via Server-Sent Events (SSE).

**Usage in browser:**
```js
const es = new EventSource(url, {
    headers: { Authorization: 'Bearer token' }
});
es.addEventListener('node.started', (e) => console.log(JSON.parse(e.data)));
```

**Event types:**
- `node.started` — A node began executing
- `node.completed` — A node finished successfully
- `node.failed` — A node encountered an error
- `execution.completed` — Full execution completed
- `execution.failed` — Full execution failed
- `execution.cancelled` — Execution was cancelled

